   "body" : "v0.15.1 release version\r\n\r\nOn F27 `bitcoin-qt` continues to connect through a proxy even when the `Connect through SOCKS5proxy` checkbox is cleared and with no `proxy=` or `onion=` in `bitcoin.conf`\r\n\r\nTo replicate: (suggested - I cannot re-prove this due to [Issue# 12498](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/12498))\r\n\r\n1. Configure a proxy. I previously had `proxy={proxy:port}` configured in `bitcoin.conf` and have set them in the GUI also.\r\n2. Remove proxy settings from `bitcoin.conf` and uncheck the {use proxy} checkboxes in Settings --> Options --> Network\r\n3. Correctly restart bitcoin-qt\r\n4. Confirm proxy is used anyway.\r\n\r\n`bitcoin-qt` should respect the setting of the {use proxy} checkboxes.",
